A 28-year-old woman, Amaka Okolie, who allegedly slapped her ex-stepmother and destroyed her necklace worth N190, 000 during an argument, has appeared at an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. Okolie, whose lives at 4, Taiwo Street, Mafoluku, Oshodi, Lagos, is charged with two counts of assault and wilful damage. He pleaded not guilty. The prosecution alleged that the defendant slapped her ex-stepmother, Mrs. Ngozi Okolie, tore her dress and cut her gold necklace valued at N190, 000, during an argument over the complainant’s refusal to leave her father’s apartment. Prosecuting Sergeant Michael Unah alleged that the defendant committed the offence on February 18, about 8:40am, at her residence. 